      <hedline>
        <hl1>For Cleaner Air in the Land of the Free</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Daniel Nemser letter disputes David Brooks April 20 Op-Ed column; contends that only industry groups have vested economic interest in proving global warming false</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>David Brooks says environmental claims put forth by environmental and industry groups are mostly equally biased (column, April 20). But this argument is completely illogical. In fact, only the industry groups have a vested economic interest in ''proving'' global warming false.</p>
        <p>DANIEL NEMSER  Ann Arbor, Mich., April 20, 2004</p>
      </block>
